title: Antares prepares to fly its last mission using Russian and Ukrainian parts
summary: Northdrop Grumman set to launch final Antares 230+ containing Russian parts from Wallops.

title: Senate committee advances orbital debris removal bill
summary: As the Senate advances a bill that would direct NASA to support missions to remove orbital debris, the agency is outlining the role it will take assisting the Commerce Department on a new space traffic coordination system.

title: Planet lays off about 10% of workforce as satellite imagery company restructures
summary: Satellite-imagery and data-analysis company Planet is restructuring and laying off 117 employees, it announced on Tuesday.

title: U.S. Space Command headquarters to remain in Colorado
summary: President Biden finally settled the drawn-out fight over the location of U.S. Space Command headquarters: It’s staying in Colorado Springs, and not moving to Huntsville, Alabama.
